Supplement Dictionary: Vitamin C

In my opinion Vitamin C is the most underrated supplement you can take in modern bodybuilding. Everybody is talking about all kind of supplements and their positive impact on your body and recovery, but somehow not many people see the advantages Vitamin C can have, especially in quite high dosages, when training hard and with high intensity. What are the biggest benefits in using L-Ascorbic Acid? Let’s check it out. 

Boost for your immune system 

Vitamin C has great benefits on your immune system and helps to shorten the time you have common colds. 

A very potent antioxidant 

Vitamin C helps to reduce cellular damages caused by so called free radicals. Doing this at the same time it reduces inflammations and cell damage in your body and thus help you to recover faster. Vitamin C also helps you to boost the production of the protein collagen which is good for wound healing, keeps your skin supple and youthful, and helps maintaining a healthy cartilage and bones. 

Helps to reduce the risk of a heart attack

Vitamin C helps to prevent negative blood-vessel changes, plaque buildup, and  hardening of the arteries that can lead to strokes, heart attacks, and other vascular diseases. Also helps maintaining healthy arteries and arterial walls. This is very important, as the arterial lining is what pumps out nitric oxide and is essential for heart health, healthy blood flow, and optimal blood pressure. 

Reduces stress and cortisol levels

It’s highly important for bodybuilders to try to keep their stress and cortisol levels as low as possible to stay out of catabolism. But every hard training increases these levels and a high doses If Vitamin C are proven to be very effective in reducing cortisol and stress levels. By doing this you help your body to be more in an anabolic state and thus build up more muscle mass. 

You see that Vitamin C has a lot of highly interesting benefits especially for anybody who’s into bodybuilding and wants to get the maximum out of it.

1000 days of GymChak
Day 374: here are my 4 staple leg day exercises that you should be doing!! They are:

⭐️ Squats - the primary muscles that these target are your:
• Gluteus maximus, minimus, and medius (basically ur bunda 🍑🍰)
• Quadriceps
• Hamstrings
And the secondary muscles include your
• Adductors
• Hip flexors
• Calves
• Core - such as your rectus abdominus (abs), obliques and erector spinae (in your back)
• If you’re doing a back squat or an overhead squat you will also use your shoulders, chest...

 (you get the idea, squats work a lot of muscles because they are an essential compound movement)

⭐️ RDLs - Primary muscles include:
• Erector Spinae
• Hamstrings 
• Trapezius (traps)
• Forearm Flexors
• Calves

⭐️ Hip Thrusts - primary muscles include:
• Glutes 🍑🍰
• Hamstrings
• Hip adductors
• Core
• Quads

⭐️ Leg press - primary muscles are basically the same as squats 🤪

All these exercises do have secondary muscles that you use but if I listed them off we’d be here for days! Smash that save button if this post has hopefully helped you learn something 🤞🏼 and have a great weekend!!

You ever feel guilty about things that are good for you?

Missing nights out with friends sucked when hearing about it the next morning. But seeing the money saved each month made me happy.

Missing vacations sucked when seeing the memories I wasn't apart of. But buying my new car made me so proud.

Missing dinners out with the girls, left me wishing I  went the next day. But my career now, which late night studying brought me, has provided so much relief.

While my friend circle got smaller, I appreciated my current friends more. The real ones knew when/why I had to grind. More importantly they knew what/when I needed some time unwind.

Point is, never feel bad for doing what's best for your life situation. Those that love you, will not only stick around but will also be there when you need a push or drink 🍻. Make those memories when you're ready ❤️

How to look in the mirror and smile 😁#freakinloveyourselffriday

Looking in the mirror can be a daunting task for some of us. Sometimes what we see can turn the whole trajectory of our day. 

That’s not how it should be. Yes, our bodies change throughout the day and throughout our life, but that does not mean you deserve to have any worse of a day than you did before. Your body is not your worth, nor will it ever be. 🤍

Sticky note affirmations are such an easy yet effective self love exercise. (you know I love simplicity☺️)

The directions are in the name:

Simply buy some sticky notes from your local target, dollar store, whatever, and write down affirmations that you want to believe about you and your body!

“It’s okay to love myself as I continue to evolve and change.”
“My body gets me through everything life throws at me.”
“I am perfect and complete just the way I am.”
“I am comfortable and confident in my own skin.”
“My body is my constant companion and works hard to accomplish what I want and need.”

Whatever it is- write it down and stick it on your mirror. Stick some on every damn mirror in the house! You deserve to be reminded of these TRUE FACTS everytime you look at yourself. 👀

This pairs affirmation with action, which is what makes them work. When you look in the mirror, you may judge yourself harshly, but pairing that judgement with visually seeing a positive affirmation, you will get through looking in the mirror more positively. The affirmation doesn't make the change, you do.💪🏼

Do you have any favorite affirmations? Mine is the first one I wrote in this caption!

Back Variations 👀🔥

En el campo de entrenamiento, existe lo que se conoce como variaciones de ejercicios. 

Una variación en un ejercicio es cuando el ejercicio tradicional lo trabajamos de una manera diferente. Puede resultar ser más fácil, complicado y/o retante. 

Aqui les dejo 2 variaciones de los ejercicios Latpulldown y Dumbbell Row

1. Incline Wide Grip Latpulldown: muchas personas trabajan este ejercicio de manera incorrecta en su postura natural (ejercicio tradicional). Al utilizar el banco levemente inclinado, obligamos al pecho a mantener contacto con el banco (pecho grande), se evita el famoso “swing” del ejercicio (manera incorrecta) y el ejercicio es más efectivo enfocándose en los dorsales anchos (latissimus dorsi) la parte más ancha de la espalda.

2. Double Arm Dumbbell Row: normalmente, este ejercicio se trabaja con una mano mientras la otra mano hace contacto con banco, rodilla o rack para mantener estabilidad y postura. Esta variación es un poco compleja ya que utilizas ambas manos para la ejecución del ejercicio. Debes mantener la postura de la espalda erguida e inclinada hacia alfrente (pecho grande). Lo complejo de este ejercicio es que utilizas otros grupos musculares que sirven como estabilizadores para mantener la postura correcta. Si no tienes estos grupos musculares fortalecidos, la postura del ejercicio se verá afectada y por ende, puedes causarte una lesión.

What to do when you compare yourself✋🏼

Do you find yourself in any point of life, at the gym, online, shopping in town find yourself comparing yourself to other people? Me too!! ✨
I’ve been comparing myself alot recently, mainly online, but don’t we all? 

When I find myself comparing myself to others and their success I try and remember 

✨ a flower doesn’t bloom over night. It takes time, patience and nourishing for it to blossom. Try not to waste time comparing yourself when you have just started and someone else is bloomed and grown! 

✨ you are UNIQUE everyone is unique. As humans we are built not to be the same we all have something to bring to table so believe in yourself and your ability 

✨ we all have flaws! We all have weaknesses and some choose not to show them on insta! your fav influencer will have something they don’t like about themselves too

✨if you work hard and believe in yourself you can accomplish anything. That’s what those you look up have done, they have worked hard!

✨Don’t give up. There’s room at the top for everyone so work hard, follow your passion and it will shine through 

✨ Working hard for what you want is important and it’s hard work to put all your efforts into it. So believe in yourself and go smash your goals 🤍

Moral of the story, work hard, be consistent and believe in yourself because everyone can succeed 💎

Just a few little things to remember when you find yourself comparing yourself to others and their success🌸

Happy Friday 💖✨

A little #tb as I’m off to go enjoy the weekend ❤️ all about being good and staying on track 90% of the time and then enjoying myself the rest of the time 🤪

This is your friendly reminder that if u go off track this weekend don’t stress about it!! All about living a balanced lifestyle ❤️ 

Progress can be made with take aways and alcohol included! Just have to be smart about it- good and staying on track 90% of the time and then eating your take aways and drinking cocktails & wine the other 10% 🥰

If you are trying to lose weight, of course the optimal way to do so is staying on track with your calories 100% of the time - but this is extremely hard to sustain so why put that pressure on yourself when you can still lose weight while not being on track all of the time? 

Staying on track most of the time will of course take longer to get results, but it is a much easier, sustainable & better way to live! 

Losing weight should be seen as a lifestyle change and not just eating healthy for a certain amount of time to lose weight fast 😓

Slow & steady wins the race always, enjoy your take away and get back to healthy eating tomorrow ❤️

WHY WE NEED FATS💛

As much as we are told to limit the amount of fat in our diet, fats can also be beneficial and are definitely needed! 

They are useful for body insulation, protecting organs and can be used for energy. It’s essential you have fats in your diet and it is our largest energy store. 

Did you know there are 9 kcal in a fat molecule? 

10% of your daily intake should be consuming saturated fats  and 30-35% of fats should be consumed within your caloric intake. Saturated fats - such as fish, avacado,walnuts & sunflower seeds. Limiting unsaturated fats reduces the risk of high cholesterol so unsaturated fats are foods such as cakes, biscuits, bacon and cheese ect. 

Don’t panic if you are tracking your macros & you go slightly over your fat intake! Just like if you were to go over any other macronutrient target It’s not the end of the world and your progress won’t decrease. Try and stick to the target and if you don’t then just make sure you try to stick to it the next day. Results take time, be patient & trust the process🤍✨

❌ 'BAD' FOOD MYTH BUSTER ❌⁣
⁣
THERE IS NO SUCH THING AS A BAD FOOD.⁣
⁣
We live in a time where our diet culture is to make you feel ashamed about how you eat, and what foods you put in your body. ⁣
Demonising foods, or a specific food group, most commonly carbs at present, can have detrimental results on our mental, and emotional health. It can make us feel bad for eating it, feel bad for wanting to eat it and can lead us to punishing ourselves for enjoying the food we actually like! ⁣
We become restrictive, and have to withstand the pressure and stress  of basing our day and social events around food. ⁣
⁣
🔥YOUR BODY NEEDS FUEL TO FUNCTION🔥⁣
⁣
A diet doesn't need to be 100% "healthy" to be healthy. ⁣
If we become less restrictive through our day-to-day, we can reduce the changes of binging, and overindulging during a low or hormonal day/ weekend. ⁣
⁣
Use the 80/20 rule. ⁣
⁣
80% of your daily calorie intake should consist of quality, nutrient rich foods. ⁣
-Whole grains⁣
-Fruits and vegetables⁣
-Lean protein⁣
-Unsaturated fats from avocados or olive oil⁣
⁣
Whilst, ⁣
⁣
20% should consist of your treats. The food you crave and can't live without. ⁣
ENJOY IT, and get rid of that feeling of guilt. ⁣
⁣
TIP ⁣
Save your treat for the afternoon/ evening. ⁣
Have something to look forward to! ⁣
⁣
Want to know more about the 80/20 diet? ⁣

PAPRIKA SOEP 🫑

Voedingswaarde: 
90 +/- kcal 

Wat heb je nodig:
- 3 (rode) paprika’s
- 1 ui
- 2 teentjes knoflook
- 2 eetlepels olijfolie
- 2 theelepels paprikapoeder
- 3 tomaten
- 700 ML water
- 1 groente bouillontablet
- 125 ML kookroom of slagroom
- basilicum 

Snij alle paprika’s, de ui en knoflook. Verhit wat olie in de pan en bak de ui en knoflook, voeg na 5 min de paprika toe en bak dit ook 5 a 10 min. 🥘

Snij de tomaten en voeg deze toe samen met de paprika poeder. Bak dit nog 2 min mee.

Voeg het water toe en breng aan de kook. Laat dit 10 min door koken. 💦

Pureer de soep en breng op smaak met peper en zout. Serveer de soep en garneer deze met kookroom en basilicum. 

Serveer deze soep met brood of als voorgerecht. 

Eetsmakkelijk! 😋

This one goes out to my fellow people pleasers!! If that’s you, listen up 🔊👂

It’s time to make yourself a priority, and not feel guilty about it.

Now, if you’re anything like me I know what you’re thinking, “ how am I supposed to be selfish without worrying about what other people think about me?”

Well, that’s the first step. I truly believe the only way to completely reach your goals is to stop caring about the opinions of others. If you’re constantly worrying about others perception of you you’re never going to improve your perception of yourself.

Now, it doesn’t have to be something drastic to start up. Say your goal is to get more sleep, maybe that means saying no to a night out here and there. you don’t have to completely cut out people in your life but you need to make yourself a priority.

Growing up I was always told that thinking of myself was selfish; however, as I’ve gotten older I realize that by not making myself a priority, I just allowed others to walk all over me.

We only have one lifetime and we can’t spend it trying to appease others. Do whatever the hell you wanna do and don’t give a damn about who gets upset. 

with that said, I hope you all have a wonderful Friday and a great weekend. And remember, if it doesn’t feed you don’t water it✨

Let’s chat habits🌸 

Something I miss about being on prep is that it was a strict lifestyle with a lot of things that became habits for me- when the show got postponed I felt a sense of loss. Although I fell off the bandwagon a bit of sticking to my routine the habits that were created stuck. 

Some of those habits are 
1. Moving my body daily (strength training, running stairs, walking, stretching etc) 
2. Starting my day early. For me personally, I was able to accomplish more when I got up earlier compared to how I used to stay up really late and be rushed in the morning. 
3. Preparing my items for the next day the night before. Since I get up early, I’m also that person who will stay in bed until my 4th alarm goes off (oops) so I have found that prepping my breakfast, my workout gear, my work supplies etc the night before has become a habit that truly has made my mornings more seamless which has also helped with managing some of my anxiety. 

Personally I find that less is more when it comes to habits, when I want to form a new one I slowly incorporate it into my life so that it is more likely to stick. 

Happy FriYAY everyone, have a good weekend and get outside 🌸☀️

For my Ladies💕🥰🌟

Period bloat is NORMAL! 🩸 

This is before and after working out. Before the gym, I was already bloated and had cramps waking up. My “morning skinny” didn’t exist and I felt very sore and swollen all around my entire body. After my workout (and cardio I might add) that was me. Couldn’t suck her in or anything, a rock solid mound of gut punching pain. 

A lot of social media tries to hide their worst angles or consumes their minds with the thought that you need to have a flat stomach 24/7. I used to get upset whenever I began my week because I knew I “wouldn’t look good” or “be able to take pictures because I looked huge”. It’s taken me a long time to accept my body for how it is. Self love and embodiment is a whole other topic but when it comes to our bloating, ladies....

 YOUR UTERINE WALLS ARE LITERALLY SHEDDING LIKE AN ANIMAL. It’s contracting and bleeding and doing it’s beautiful thing only WE as women get to experience. Yes it SUCKS but I’m thankful for my body being able to function as it prepares me for the day I want to have a family. I’m learning to stop complaining and learning to appreciate all that my body does and can do for me, even when it brings on pain, loving your body for all its purpose makes it all worth it. Don’t ever forget that🥰

Always check up on YOURSELF & on your loved ones xx

Es la forma más pura de la proteína de suero y está compuesto en un 90% o más por proteína pura. Se le considera una proteína completa, lo que significa que posee todos los aminoácidos necesarios para la dieta diaria, con niveles especialmente elevados de aminoácidos de cadena ramificada (BCAAs).
Beneficios: Rápida absorción (Entre 2 o 3 horas), es completamente digerible por cualquier persona, ayuda a la perdida de grasa y ayuda a la recuperación muscular y al rendimiento físico.

GREATNESS IS WITHIN 🔥 

A very famous quote, but very true.

We all have the ability to achieve great things both inside and outside of the gym.

In order to achieve the greatness it requires the action. The thoughts themselves are not good enough❌

I hear many people say “I’ll never be able to do that” or “I’ll never look like that” - when really we all have the same capabilities, it just depends how much you’re willing to put towards it 🤷🏽‍♂️

My advice to you is to think about what’s holding you back - is it your ability? Or are you not trying hard enough.

My second piece of advice is to take that first step. Without the first step nothing can happen from that greatness within.

If you’re looking for help taking that first step with your fitness goals then send me a quick DM if you want to find out more💪🏼

WHAT I EAT IN A DAY 🍽

This is my day of eating yesterday. It’s unrestrictive, balanced, and yummy!! 

This is not what I eat everyday, some days are healthier than others, but I allow myself those days where I want more sugar/carbs/fats :) 

Breakfast: porridge with a teaspoon of Nutella and a fruit topping, my favourite breakfast and I pretty much eat this 5 times per week

Snack: protein bar. Depending on my plans, level of hunger, I maybe have a mid-morning snack, or may not. Sometimes I’ll just have a big late breakfast. 

Lunch: left over dinner for lunch, fajita pasta, 😍, with someone homemade garlic bread with Parmesan 😗🤌🏽

Snack: pop chips and dairylea, because I just couldn’t wait while I was cooking my dinner 🙃 

Dinner: chicken noodle stir fry 🥢

After dinner snacks: M&S pudding, not worth the calories 😭 looks amazing, tasted average 😔, and an apple 🍎

To anyone waiting for the right time to start your fitness journey;

It’s easy to get stuck in the “I will start on Monday” or “I will start when this thing is over” loop. But there is a given that you must remember: 

Time will go by regardless of what you do. 

This week will finish whether you get those workouts in or not, and whether you eat your veggies or eat McDonalds. 

The next month will go by. And it will go by without stopping to make sure you’ve practiced self-care or kept up with your fitness plan. 

Time will continue to pass, you cannot change that. What you CAN change is what you do in that time, what habits you build, and what narratives you let guide your life. 

Time will go by, but you could wake up a very different person in a month, 6 months or a year.

Whatever goals you have are not going to come more quickly to you if you don’t start them. Start now! Everything you need to pursue your goals is inside you. Everyone on a fitness and health journey is constantly learning. You are not alone. Ask for help when you need it, and have so much faith in yourself!

Everything you need is inside you. So just start ☀️

caption:
🪑 Being physically active does not completely offset the negative effects of sitting 🪑⁠
⁠
🏋🏻‍♀️ We all know that sitting all day is bad. But it turns out you have to do more than just exercise at the end of your day to avoid negative effects of sitting like cancer, heart disease and diabetes⁠
⁠
🔍 A review of 47 studies found that prolonged sitting was strongly linked to negative health outcomes, regardless of exercise levels. Although the negative effects were even greater for people who barely exercised ⁠
⁠
👩‍💼 Tips if you have a desk job⁠
- get a standing desk ⁠
- go for a few short walks during your workday⁠
- pair movement with another habit like squatting while waiting for your tea⁠
⁠
☝🏼 So remember: minimizing sedentary time is just as important for health as a nutritious diet and regular exercise⁠
⁠
⁠
⁠
Source: Biswas A. et al. (2015)⁠
⁠

It was a little cooler earlier this week so garage closed for this one 👎🏽. This lower body day was a change up in exercises so let’s jump right into it!

Clip 1: elevated toes RDLs.

Clip 2: elevated heels squats.

Clip 3: lunge back to a single leg balanced calf raise. This is a good full body movement and challenged me, especially with the calf raise!

Clip 4: hip internal rotation with a band. This was working those inner thigh muscles along with the quads and glutes while bing in the squat.

Clip 5: landmine squats.

Clip 6: landmine deadlifts (sorta). I wish I could have had my body elevated more since I couldn’t squat down quite as much as you would in a deadlift with handles I was using but there was still a good burn!

Remember a body in motion, stays in motion. A body at rest will stay there until acted upon. So get up and get in motion!

Haz oído hablar de la teoría de la confusión muscular❓ 

dice que debes entrenar de forma diferente para que el músculo no se acostumbre a lo mismo. 
.
🚷Esta teoría es totalmente falsa, los músculos no se confunden y no se sorprenden,  lo que si me sorprende es la cantidad de entrenadores que dicen esta estupidez, los músculos se estimulan y generan adaptaciones fisiológicas según el grado de estímulo que le des.
.
♻️La base del progreso se mide principalmente aplicando sobrecarga progresiva✅, es decir haciendo incrementos de volumen y de intensidad paulatinamente, el volumen de entrenamiento recuperable de cada sujeto es diferente y tiene un límite, en cambio ir subiendo los pesos a medida ganes fuerza es realmente la clave, por ejemplo si empiezas haciendo sentadilla con 50kg 10 reps, cada 2 semanas debes hacer pequeños incrementos de peso y verás que al cabo de varias semanas estarás haciendo 10 rep con 60kg o más (medición de progreso real).

En conclusión la sobrecarga progresiva es lo que realmente importa para tú progreso,  a parte de ser miembro y entrenar en ⭕️ @shapenshake ⭕️con resultados garantizados

Consult with a personal trainer if you need help with your physical fitness.

Consult with a Registered Dietitian if you need help with your nutrition.

Consult with a doctor if you need help with misfiring body parts or extraordinary bodily functions.

Stop overcomplicating it.
Stop following 50 IG influencers who are each telling you something different.
Stop expecting an RD to perform the duties of a doctor.
Stop expecting personal trainers to perform the duties of RDs.

There’s overlap sometimes, sure.
And if you find that, good for you!

Just a friendly reminder that there are specialists for a reason. Practice using them for what they’re good at, instead of relying on one—or multiple—people to do the job others are trained AND LICENSED to do.

Exercise IS essential. Do you agree? ⁣
⁣
Whether gyms are open or closed...exercise should be a priority. ⁣
⁣
Not just for aesthetic reasons, but for your actual health.⁣
⁣
Sometimes we might dread a workout, but you know how GOOD it feels after you’re done. With those post workout endorphins flowing and energy levels increasing.⁣
⁣

⁣
A lot of sad things.⁣
⁣
A lot of sick people.⁣
⁣
But what isn’t stressed enough is how important health & nutrition is.⁣
⁣
Do you know how many illnesses and diseases can be prevented by properly fueling your body and exercising? ⁣
⁣
If you don’t take care of yourself now, I can promise you that health problems will be on the rise for you in the future.⁣
⁣
Don’t let your future self deal with it. Don’t keep pushing it off. Don’t think that medicine will be the answer.⁣
⁣
The best medicine is to step into a routine that works for you.⁣
⁣
Start doing workouts that you enjoy.⁣
⁣
Start adding in healthy food into your diet.⁣
⁣

You just gotta take action, Now!⁣
⁣

Weight isn't the be all and end all. The muscle doesn't care what is on the bar. It just knows it can or it can't. 

Every day, every session is an opportunity to learn something. 

Pay attention to what's going on with your body and in your head. All the lessons are there.

⁣
HI friends it has been quite a while since I last posted! This week has been both draining but fulfilling at the same time! I can’t ‘publicly’ disclose too much, but I have been working in hospital with mostly a geriatric population & they are the absolute CUTEST humans. I’ve learnt/experienced so much already! Downsides - my bed time has been close to 8:30-9 ish and my sprained ankle is SUPER swollen from being up on my feet all day :( My left ankle is literally double the size of my right lmfao buttttt I am officially getting it checked out today so fingers crossed! 🥲⁣
⁣
Other updates with my life if you haven’t r eally been following my stories: I impulsively purchased a squat rack along with a bench, barbells and plates LOL. Don’t ask me about my bank account thanks!! I honestly do not think the gyms will be opening here anytime soon.. 🙃 and I can usually get pretty creative with the equipment I had, but I was sick of sketchy bench set ups and never knowing how far away we are from the gyms opening.. ⁣
⁣
I realize not everyone has all of the equipment in this workout video, BUT my biggest advice is to get creative! (Or you can save this for when the gyms open!) 😁⁣
⁣
ANYWAY - Ill be providing more variety and home friendly workouts in the future so stay tuned & MAKE SURE TO GIVE IT A SAVVEEEE & SHARE (saving helps me growww so I appreciate it tons :’)) ⁣

✅INTRODUCTION

📍Pulmonary embolism (PE) is a blockage of one of the pulmonary arteries in the lungs. In most cases, a deep venous thrombosis (DVT) forms in the leg. Once dislodged, the thrombus travels to the lungs where it occludes the pulmonary artery. The condition is a medical emergency that requires prompt diagnosis and treatment to ensure patient survival.

✅PATHOLOGICAL PROCESS

📍Thrombus formation occurs due to stasis in the deep veins, especially at the calf. The patient's initial cardiorespiratory status, and size and number of emboli affects the severity of changes in pulmonary blood flow and respiration. A small blockage of the pulmonary artery may not provoke symptoms, while a large embolus can be fatal.

📍In the latter case, pulmonary embolism causes wasted ventilation as it increases the alveoli dead space, resulting in a ventilation-perfusion mismatch and an increase in pulmonary artery pressures and right ventricular work.  Consequently, there is eventual right heart failure, followed by the left side of the heart due to decrease in blood volume and coronary perfusion to the left ventricle. Cardiac muscle dysfunction ensues, and the heart ceases to pump blood.

✅PHYSIOTHERAPY IMPLICATIONS

📍Mobility is vital to patient recovery following PE. Following anticoagulation and thrombolytic therapies, bed rest is typically prescribed followed by inpatient therapy. The main aim of physiotherapy is to restore a clear lung field and oxygen uptake to optimal level. This may be achieved through chest physiotherapy and then progressed to include endurance exercises such as walking or bicycle ergometry.

- Welp, here it is... my 2 year transformation. Since I turn 19 in 2 days, I wanted to post this before my birthday. I started working out because I was underweight and didn’t like the way I looked. During the start of my journey I only weighed 115lbs and didn’t really know what to do. I started doing research and kept staying consistent with my workouts. At first, it was really hard for me to eat a lot because of my appetite. During my senior year of high school I had many occasions were I didn’t go to the gym because of swim season. I had to participate in many events/meets since I was the captain of the team. After the season ended, I was really motivated and started to get back to the gym. I started training 6 days a week for 2 and a half hours and kept pushing myself everyday. I ended up gaining 30lbs by the end of summer 2020. Even though I gained some size, I also gained a lot of fat. I had times where I looked at myself in the mirror and was very upset. But I knew I had to keep bulking... I kept training harder and harder, adding more volume to my workouts. Here I am now weighing around 160lbs. This is just the beginning... Stay consistent and trust the process...

Different kind of transformation post today.
-
Just under 3 months between these pictures and the difference is night and day, both on the inside and outside.
-
On the left we are slap bang in the middle of lockdown, had nowhere to train, business was at it’s worst and feeling very mentally drained from lockdown, which I’m sure majority of people can relate to. I had lost nearly every bit of drive I had in me in every aspect. I can honestly say I have never felt like that in my adult life before.
-
Since stepping away from Ireland into a place where there is a taste of normality it didn’t take long to come back around to my normal self 😂 Simple things like the environment of a gym, walking around town and people out shopping, having conversations with different people (this takes some getting used to I legit couldn’t speak for a few days 😂), these are the things that gets that spark back in you to start living life with a bit of normality and passion.
-
Better times are coming 🤞🏻 We are nearly at the end of this rollercoaster and for anyone who is struggling, stay strong 💪🏻 We’ve had enough of our lives taken from us, use it as fuel to set yourself up for a year of new opportunities 🙌🏻

WHY YOU SHOULDN'T BE FOLLOWING LOW CALORIE DIETS

although a lot of people know that eating in a calorie deficit is the only way to lose fat, a lot still think that the lower calories they eat = the better.

HOWEVER, PLEASE REMEMBER: FOOD ISN'T SOMETHING YOU NEED TO 'BURN OFF'. YOUR BODY NEEDS FOOD TO FUNCTION. INTERNALLY, YOUR ORGANS ARE WORKING HARD TO KEEP YOU ALIVE, IT NEEDS CALORIES TO WORK. 

here are ways that LOW CALORIE DIET NEGATIVELY EFFECTS YOUR INTERNAL BODY FUNCTIONS: 
1. Reproductive Functions 🍼 
during a low calorie diet, the body cuts down production of sex hormones (testosterone, estrogen, progesterone and other androgens)
for women this can lead to:
⮕ irregular or lost of menstrual cycles
⮕ hormonal imbalance
⮕ pre menopause symptomps or early menopause
it can lead to infertility for both men and women
2. Cognitive Functions 🧠 
the brain needs a lot of energy constantly, a low calorie diet can slow down brain metabolism which may result in
⮕ being more forgetful
⮕ brain fog
⮕ less creative
3. Repair and Restoration 🩸 
remember, our body's tissues are always being broken down and rebuilt/replenished inside our body.
thus, if people who exercise regularly (active individuals) don't eat enough, they won't recover properly
4. Vitamins and Minerals 🥒 
due to a low energy intake, it's hard to reach all micronutrients such as vitamins and minerals- when in fact, we need them for a healthy metabolism.

HAPPY FRIDAY🤍

I woke up with period cramps today and just wanted to stay in bed all day… but then I decided to get up and start my day off slowly. It’s so important to take care of yourself and today that meant starting off slowly but still getting up and giving this day the chance to change for the better. 
So I got up, put on comfy clothes and got ready to take some cute pictures. It’s those little things that can make your mood change and make you feel better.

I don’t think that I’m going to do a lot today. I’ll do some stretching with the @toneandsculptapp and I’m looking forward to lots of cuddles with my dog. And that’s okay. It’s okay to take some time off. It’s okay to wake up not feeling great because we all feel like that sometimes. Just remember a day has 24 hours and if your day starts off bad that doesn’t mean it has to go on like that. Do something for yourself today and give this day the chance to be beautiful🤍

When I was young I had such big dreams and aspirations, and at the time I thought I’d stop at nothing to be the best.

I’ve gone from going to school for anthropology with a discipline in archaeology, to being a village drunk and socialite, and I worked in the music industry managing rap/hip hop artists. In every phase of life I was always hungry for more and never felt satisfied because I always felt like I had to be the best, and never accepted myself simply DOING my best.

I think the pressure of living up to societal standards of being prestigious, well liked, and successful really blindsided my reality of what being happy is about. 

Your title, your accomplishments, your status is all for nothing if you aren’t nourishing your mind and body and feel whole. 

These days I do something I thought I’d never do - I work a normal ass job, wake up early, train and work out and stay active multiple times a day, eat foods that fuel me, keep to myself, and for the first time in my entire life I feel satisfied. You don’t have to be anyone or live up to anything, we all simply exist in this world living our little lives. 

Touch the hearts of those you come across with kindness, get fresh air and wave at dogs when they pass by, find hobbies that you can do alone that enrich your life, pay your bills, treat yourself, be humble, and do your best. 

We are so lucky to get to experience life, cherish it 💓

How can you build healthy habits?! 

I want to be real with you guys and tell you that I sometimes catch myself falling into a moment of bad habits. I might question whether I should eat something or not because it’s not “good for me” and I always remind myself that I have come too far forward to take any steps back. 

I do not allow those moments of negativity to control me anymore

This is your reminder that:

✨The number on the scale does not define you
✨One bad day is not a bad life
✨You won’t loose progress by treating yourself or taking rest days
✨Fitness is a lifestyle

Here are some tips for creating sustainable habits:

🌸Find your WHY
🌸Celebrate the small wins
🌸Do not restrict yourself! This will only lead to binging and further restrictions 
🌸Focus on balance

Your mindset is 80% of your success. 💭

Have you ever heard this quote by Walt Disney? 
‘If you can dream it, you can do it.’ 🙋‍♂️

I think it’s one of the most inspiring quotes out there. 🙌
I believe you can achieve anything with the right mindset.

👇Here are the best tips for you👇

✅Take pride in how your body looks like based on how hard you train, not comparing yourself to others.
👉Let’s get one fact straight, no one has better or worse body than you.
Some of us started our journey years ago and some of us start today.

✅Set priorities. Training over the aesthetics goals.
👉Your attitude towards training will improve and you’ll be buzzing to get your next session done once you switch your mind from how’s my body looking to how strong I am.

✅Consider all variables when measuring your progress.
👉Weight alone is not the best measurement of your progress.
There are a few more variables you should keep in mind like your strength, your size and how you look in the mirror.

✅Focus on things you can control.
👉You can control what you eat, what exercises you do, how you manage stress on the daily basis or how much sleep you’re getting each night. That’s plenty to keep you busy.

✅Get competitive, but only with yourself.
👉Imagine a competition day. If you knew you have to perform at your best today you could wake up early and prepare a nutritious breakfast to maximise your energy before competition. You could avoid eating certain foods because these could make you feel bloated and therefore affect your performance. Now, try to make your day just like it was a competition day.

Be patient with your progress because if you quit you will never know how close you were to achieving your goal. 💯
 
How will you change your training mindset today to get yourself closer to your goals? 👊

Let me know in comment or message me. 🙏🏻

I don’t use this insta anymore but I wanted to document for myself going from 76kg > 82/83kg. Left was start of March and right was this morning.
This isn’t a result from lockdown training as such, i became ill with something and it’s manageable now but count me blessings I’m no longer so tired & in pain and can train whenever I want.

As I mentioned, I won’t be using this insta, it’s good to look at for me really & it served it’s purpose for when I needed an outlet.

Moral of this post is If you get an illness, don’t be a stubborn bloke, was an awful 3 months not knowing what was going on, this isn’t a motivational post but having the gym and people around kept my head from falling off over and over again 

Big up the boys and T I love yas the world and more 🦸🏻‍♀️👨‍👦‍👦

When you plant a seed, don’t expect it to germinate and grow straight away 🌱 

At 16/17 years old I weighed 17.8 Stone (113kg). But that same 16/17 year old told himself that enough is enough and no matter how long it takes, I’m going be fitter physically and mentally. Fast forward 5/6 years and this I me now weighing 13.3 Stone (85kg).

People that know me knew how big I was but I didn’t care until various things started to happen. I felt like I didn’t fit in and was just unfit to do anything. 

Last week was the first ever time I’ve ever taken off my shirt in public which was a major achievement for me. People before have asked me why I don’t show my body but I brushed it under the carpet. But the real reason was that I just didn’t have the confidence and self belief and really didn’t love the way I looked. I was scared because in the past people have judged me because of the size I was and throw hurtful comments which crushes your self esteem. But I had to overcome that fear and let it go💪🏾

Currently I’m on the last week of the @swench_online_coaching @troy.hemus @scott_swench 6 week challenge and I’ve learnt a lot about dieting and also my own body in regards to its limitations and drive and I wanna thank these guys for the plan and support given.

Finally, for the person that is in the same position I was and still in, this journey isn’t a sprint, so take time, stay consistent and motivate yourself and the people around to keep in shape physically and mentally 🙏🏾

•Mix all together 1 Cup applesauce, 1/2 cup almond or peanut butter, 2/3 cup cocoa, 1-2 scoops of protein powder. 2-3 tbls of erythritol sugar free sweetener (or whichever kind you like!)

Coming at you with a BACK and BICEPS workout! Back days are honestly my favorite thing to train, a close second is biceps, so I'm excited for you guys to check this one out!

🏎straight arm pull-downs 4x 12
🏎kayak rows 3x 10 each side
🏎lat pull-downs 3x 15
🏎underhand close grip pull-downs 3x 15
🏎alternating hammer curls 3x 10 each arm
🏎zottman curls 3x 12
🏎superhero curls 4x 15

Straight arm pull downs are one of my favorite exercises of all time, I swear I do it every week😅 make sure to have a slight bend in your knees and elbows to prevent any injuries! Kayak rows are very similar to straight arm pull downs, but we are leading with one arm, kind of like how we would row a boat or a kayak! I honestly don't know the name of the last exercise but it makes me feel like I'm a super hero trying to hold onto a cliff and save someone from falling off of it💀 but anyways! Hope you enjoy this workout! Don't forget to LIKE and SAVE it for later!!

🎥Shoutout to Aly for being a great camera woman on the first exercise!

caption:
Motivation doesn’t come handed on a plate all the time. Sometimes you have to really talk to yourself and find the discipline to make yourself do things. Sometimes you won’t have any motivation and you won’t be able to talk yourself around. And sometimes you just have to put your comfort blanket on (or cardigan in my case) and go with the flow until you find yourself again. 

It’s finally Friday! I’ve had a strange week. I’ve really found my feet with all things fitness and nutrition and feel I’m in a good place with that side of things and it’s feeling amazing. But I’ve really struggled to drag myself out of bed in the mornings and go for the walk, run or bike ride that I normally would before starting work. And I’ve felt so sluggish for not doing it and that feeling has genuinely lasted all day, but I’ve still had no motivation to do it the following day. I’ve really beat myself up for it, but we don’t need to. Sometimes we do just need to look at all that we are achieving and not give ourselves a hard time for being a bit slack with something else at the same time. So now I’ve had a bit of a break, and I’m doing something wild here and starting afresh tomorrow. Yes on a Saturday, because we shouldn’t just wait for Monday all the time or it’ll never happen. 

Do what you need to do, whether that’s in the form of choosing to stay in bed an extra half hour because you appreciate a lie in and slow start to the day, or jumping up and out of bed at 5am and throwing yourself into your day. Do whatever makes you happy and gives you a sense of satisfaction but whatever it is, don’t beat yourself up if it’s not the option you ‘should’ be choosing. There is no right or wrong. There is you, as you are 🥰✨

Train For Your Mental Health🧠 

With it being mental health awareness week I thought I share a little something about much I value training for mental health.

I would say there was a good 2-3 years where I was a little lost, as any young person may feel at that time in their life, but training was the one thing that honestly kept me going...

Knowing that I had that 1 hour a day to escape whatever else was going on & focus on myself for a bit was what I looked forward to everyday. Not to say there wasn’t days where I didn’t want to, trust me there’s plenty days, but it’s that reminder of how good you feel after you get past that little bit of suffering. And getting through one bit of suffering, will help you to surpass the next battle you may face.

Once you learn & understand the value of training, not just for your physical health, but also mental, then you’ll start to see other aspects of you life come together as well.

Training (and I mean proper training, not just doing an incline walk on the treadmill for 20 minutes) will teach you so many lessons:
* Resilience
* Discipline
* Consistency
* Humility
* Tolerance Of Physical & Mental Pain

These days, I like to finish my workouts with something for the mind. So to that dark place & come out of it feeling that sense of euphoria knowing what you have just accomplished.

For Time:
50 Cal Assault Bike
50 KB Swings
50 Air Squats
100 Butterfly Sit Ups
50 Air Squats
50 KB Swings
50 Cal Assault Bike

Simple but a test. (Especially after a squat session...)

You’ll learn about yourself the more you do sh*t like this that hurts you. But you’ll also be a lot strong for it.

So if you’re someone who is struggling in any way at all, I urge you to train. Whatever your capabilities, just do something that is going to be tough. Push yourself through it & see what type of person comes out of it at the end.

It’s more than just training,
It’s more than just looking good,
It’s a life changer,
And sometimes a life saver.

Today, we are hitting the floor with a complete core workout👏🏼 This circuit will target your back, abs, obliques, and shoulders👇🏼

•Workout Breakdown•
1. Superman 30sec
2. Pike push-up 30sec
3. Russian twist 30sec
4. Flutter kicks 30sec
5. Side plank 30sec (right)
6. Side plank 30sec (left)

**Repeat twice through without breaks (6min a set) and complete three sets (8min total) 

•Pointers for this pointers•
1. For swimmers, relax at the bottom and squeeze butt/lower back to raise
2. For pike push-up, engage your core and lightly tape head to floor
3. For Russian twists, keep legs off the ground. When twisting, thought hands to floor on each side
4. For flutter kicks, place hands by your butt to safeguard lower backs. Keep core tight and the flutters six inches above the ground
5. For side plank, keep shoulder directly over elbow and hips aligned. Push up though your shoulder, avoid sagging into it. If you would like to make this harder, plank on your hand then lift your upper leg

🍋 LEMON CHICKEN WITH ORZO🍋
•
•
Stole this recipe from @tasteofhome and it did not disappoint! Super easy, quick, and YUMMY! Andddd As an added bonus, its macro friendly :) 
•
•
What you’ll need: 
🍋1/3 cup of all purpose flour 
🍋1 tsp of garlic powder 
🍋1 lb of chicken breast (butterflied)
🍋1 3/4 cups of chicken bone broth 
🍋1 1/4 cup of uncooked Orzo pasta 
🍋Spinach (as much or as little as you want)
🍋1 cup of grape tomatoes sliced 
🍋 3 tbsp of fresh lemon juice 
🍋basil to top 
•
•
1. Mix flower and garlic powder in a small bowl. Cut chicken into inch cubes. Dip chicken in flour mixture to coat and shake off excess.
2. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add diced chicken and cook until no longer pink. Remove from Pan and keep warm. 
3. In the same Pan, bring chicken broth to a boil. Add in orzo. Return back to a boil, then reduce heat and let simmer 8-10 min while covered. 
4. Once orzo is cooked, stir in spinach, tomato and basil and remove from heat. Add in lemon juice and stir in chicken. Voila! 
•
•

Let’s talk Mindset!!

•So today i finished sixth form... 2 years of pure stress!! Throughout the 2 years my mental health declined so quickly I couldn’t catch up with it and I never took time away for myself to allow my brain to relax! 

•I can’t explain how important taking time for yourself to relax and chill is! Allowing your mind to repair and get stronger is just as important as allowing your muscles to repair and get stronger 💪🏻

•It’s easier said than done to always be positive, and in no way am I saying I’m always positive but it’s always something to work toward 🤍

•There’s always a silver lining even if it does seem like it miles and miles away!! There’s always someone to talk to and my DMs are always open!

Skipping 😃

Today for my warm up I said I’d change it up and picked the skipping rope. 

I haven’t skipped properly in over 20 years as you can tell by my technique 😂 

I found it great but really tough and wasn’t long warming up 💦 

Whether you do it at the start of your workout , or even a finisher give it a try! 

Get the timer out and set a time to go for. If you break stride just keep it going until the time is up rest and then set that timer again. 

I only done 5 mins and was sweating heavy after it.

🔥1 minute on rest for 30 seconds and then go again until you done 5 minutes work!

I will master skipping with a bit of practice in a few weeks and not just jump up and down like a mad man 😂

Minha academia é o mundo. 
E ela está sempre aberta. 

O que mais me fascinou na calistenia foi que eu não tenho desculpa de não treinar. 

Antes quando eu viajava eu não treinava. Se a viagem fosse de 2 semanas, seriam duas semanas sem treinar. Depois que descobri o mundo de possibilidades e a liberdade que a calistenia trás isso não aconteceu mais. Talvez tenha treinado menos por conta da rotina corrida em algum momento nos últimos 5 anos. Houve um período da vida (fim do ano passado) que eu estava tão cansado e ocupado que treinava 1 vez por semana apenas. Nas melhores semanas treinava 2 vezes. Porém ajustando minha alimentação fui capaz de manter um percentual de gordura relativamente baixo e conquistei o que perdi em pouco tempo. 

Não importa onde, não importa a circunstância. Calistenia vai te permitir treinar em qualquer lugar, com ou sem equipamento. 

Seja um exterminador de desculpas. 

Stay hard.

🍋 LEMON CHICKEN WITH ORZO🍋
•
•
Stole this recipe from @tasteofhome and it did not disappoint! Super easy, quick, and YUMMY! Andddd As an added bonus, its macro friendly :) 
•
•
What you’ll need: 
🍋1/3 cup of all purpose flour 
🍋1 tsp of garlic powder 
🍋1 lb of chicken breast (butterflied)
🍋1 3/4 cups of chicken bone broth 
🍋1 1/4 cup of uncooked Orzo pasta 
🍋Spinach (as much or as little as you want)
🍋1 cup of grape tomatoes sliced 
🍋 3 tbsp of fresh lemon juice 
🍋basil to top 
•
•
1. Mix flower and garlic powder in a small bowl. Cut chicken into inch cubes. Dip chicken in flour mixture to coat and shake off excess.
2. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add diced chicken and cook until no longer pink. Remove from Pan and keep warm. 
3. In the same Pan, bring chicken broth to a boil. Add in orzo. Return back to a boil, then reduce heat and let simmer 8-10 min while covered. 
4. Once orzo is cooked, stir in spinach, tomato and basil and remove from heat. Add in lemon juice and stir in chicken. Voila!

Let’s talk Mindset!!

•So today i finished sixth form... 2 years of pure stress!! Throughout the 2 years my mental health declined so quickly I couldn’t catch up with it and I never took time away for myself to allow my brain to relax! 

•I can’t explain how important taking time for yourself to relax and chill is! Allowing your mind to repair and get stronger is just as important as allowing your muscles to repair and get stronger 💪🏻

•It’s easier said than done to always be positive, and in no way am I saying I’m always positive but it’s always something to work toward 🤍

•There’s always a silver lining even if it does seem like it miles and miles away!! There’s always someone to talk to and my DMs are always open! 

And in the words of @antmiddleton sometimes it’s « mind over muscle »

•DM me for more info 🤍

Skipping 😃

Today for my warm up I said I’d change it up and picked the skipping rope. 

I haven’t skipped properly in over 20 years as you can tell by my technique 😂 

I found it great but really tough and wasn’t long warming up 💦 

Whether you do it at the start of your workout , or even a finisher give it a try! 

Get the timer out and set a time to go for. If you break stride just keep it going until the time is up rest and then set that timer again. 

I only done 5 mins and was sweating heavy after it.

🔥1 minute on rest for 30 seconds and then go again until you done 5 minutes work!

I will master skipping with a bit of practice in a few weeks and not just jump up and down like a mad man 😂

Deadlifts have still been feeling pretty good, worked up to a top set of 4 with 345. Along with a couple of other back workouts. Going to be attempting 395 soon so stay tuned for that! 405 is in sight, potentially even more!

❌deadlift 6 sets of 8-4 reps (as you increase the weight every set, aim for a lower rep range) for a top set of 4

❌isolated seated rows, 4 sets of 12- 14 reps each arm (get that full contraction when you pull back) 

❌lat pull downs, 4x10-6 reps (increase weight after each set for a top set of 6) 

❌ seated cable rows: 10-14 reps 

❌reversed flys: 3 sets 12-14 reps (really focus on the squeeze)

❌pull ups (didn’t get to record them) but to finish off try to do as many pull ups possible for 2 sets

Minha academia é o mundo. 
E ela está sempre aberta. 

O que mais me fascinou na calistenia foi que eu não tenho desculpa de não treinar. 

Antes quando eu viajava eu não treinava. Se a viagem fosse de 2 semanas, seriam duas semanas sem treinar. Depois que descobri o mundo de possibilidades e a liberdade que a calistenia trás isso não aconteceu mais. Talvez tenha treinado menos por conta da rotina corrida em algum momento nos últimos 5 anos. Houve um período da vida (fim do ano passado) que eu estava tão cansado e ocupado que treinava 1 vez por semana apenas. Nas melhores semanas treinava 2 vezes. Porém ajustando minha alimentação fui capaz de manter um percentual de gordura relativamente baixo e conquistei o que perdi em pouco tempo. 

Não importa onde, não importa a circunstância. Calistenia vai te permitir treinar em qualquer lugar, com ou sem equipamento. 

Seja um exterminador de desculpas. 

Stay hard.

-
We achieved this results by implementing Non-negotiable goals everyday 🎯

Here’s mine 💅🏽

💃🏼 Gym every morning before work - I feel i have morning energy then

💃🏼 3-4ltrs of water a day- sometimes more just depends on my workouts🏋🏼‍♀️ 
💃🏼 Step target of 16k steps per day - I do normally do more 🚶🏼‍♀️ 
💃🏼 4/5 weighted gym sessions a week 
💃🏼 Atleast 25mins of cardio 5times a week
💃🏼 Hitting my protein goal of 120g a day 
💃🏼 Being kind to myself 
💃🏼 Hitting my calorie goals daily 
-

Lower ab workout — remember that little pouch you have on your stomach most likely will never go away because it’s supposed to be there!! But instead do these ab workouts to strengthen your core and make your body feel better 🤍 

To challenge yourself take little to no break in between each of these workouts you’ll really feel it!!

🔅20 Crunch kicks 
🔅30 (15 each leg) Scissors w leg grab 
🔅40 Penguins — don’t rush through these! 
🔅15 Leg lift w hip lift — sit on your hands in this hurts too your lower back too much .. I know sitting on your hands really isn’t ideal but I think it’s better than hurting your lower back from rolling up 
🔅20 (10 each leg) dead bugs

BURNT OUT💤

Emotional, mentally and physically exhausted lately so I have (wells Abs my trainer) has made the decision to put me on a deload for a few days just so my body can recovery and I can regain some energy. These last few months I’ve put so much work into finishing my degree, up early, later nights, bettering myself and my body and right now it’s all become to much and I’ve crashed massively.

So thankful for the decision to deload because my body feels like it’s been hit by a bus and the rest is definitely needed. Still going to be eating the same because even if I’m not working out for a few days my body still requires fuel 💪🏻 

Don’t be afraid to take a few days/weeks away from exercise and just REST your health and well-being is so much more important than progressing in the gym. 

So for today I’m napping and that’s about as good as it gets. Don’t get me wrong I will feel incredibly guilty for it as I always feel like I need to be doing something productive with my time but right now the most productive thing I can do is rest so that’s exactly what I’m going to do 🤩

Did someone say PROTEIN PB CUPS? 😧
-
I don’t know about you, but PB cups are one of my FAV treats! So, one day I figured id make a protein packed recipe. BOY I AM GLAD I DID. 🥵
-
Not to mention the recipe is simple and calls for only 3 FLIPPIN’ INGREDIENTS. ⬇️
-
1️⃣ @1upnutrition ’s chocolate peanut butter blast protein powder
2️⃣ Peanut butter 
3️⃣ Dark chocolate 
-
Let’s dive right into the instructions. Swipe right to follow along with pictures.💥
-
🥜 Plop 32g of PB in a bowl. I use @crazyrichards & I am in LOVE.
🥜 Toss in 1/2 scoop of 1up Nutrition’s chocolate peanut butter blast protein powder.
🥜 Mix until you get the consistancy in the photo I took. Really press down and mix it up real good.
🥜 Place the mixture at the bottom of cupcake papers.
🥜 Put 15g of 85% (or whatever kind ya like) dark chocolate in a bowl. Place in microwave for 20 seconds, mix, then back in the microwave for another 30 seconds.
🥜 Pour on top of mixture in the cupcake paper.
🥜 Place in freezer for 2-3 hours, then BAM! FINISHED!
-
Macros 🔽
Calories: 328
Carbs: 11.5g 
Fat: 24.5g 
Protein: 21.5g
-

↩︎
「プリッとしたお尻を作りたい」
↩︎
今は多くの女性がSNSでフォーカスを当てているのが引き上がった丸いプリッとしたお尻🍑
様々なワークアウトがあり、24hジムではほとんどの女性がヒップのワークアウトを時間を掛けて行っている姿を見掛けます😊
↩︎ 
そしてそれはもはや、男性にも関係のない話ではなさそう☝🏽男でも、プリッとお尻の方がセクシーですよね！
↩︎
このアブダクションは、プリッとしたお尻には欠かせないワークアウトです😌
↩︎
中臀筋にアプローチするこのワークアウト、この動画みたいに、マシンの背もたれは無視して、前傾して行っている人よく見かけませんか？？👀
これはお尻の横側にある中臀筋の"上部"に効かせる方法です☝🏽
↩︎
中臀筋のボディメイクでの役割は
📌大臀筋を引き上げる
📌脂肪を引き上げる
です！
プリッとしたお尻は、もはやただ筋肉をつけるのではなく、ある程度脂肪もつけてふっくらさせる時代🤔
中臀筋は、そんな脂肪組織さえも引き上げてくれます😳
なので、プリッとしたお尻には必要不可欠なワークアウトなんですねー♫
↩︎
そして、背もたれにもたれかかるフォームよりも、しっかり前傾して行うフォームの方が、より中臀筋の上部を使えるので、お尻の位置が高くなり、脚長効果にも繋がるんです😆
こりゃプリケツを手に入れたい女性、男性はやらないと損なワークアウトですね♫
↩︎
↩︎
ポイント🍑
📌股関節から折れる様に上半身をしっかり前傾
📌手を組み、股関節が開く瞬間にその手も外に意識する事で、神経の連動性により股関節を外に開きやすくなります
📌胸郭を引き上げ、胸椎は伸展を意識します。そうする事でより効果的に中臀筋へ刺激を送ることができます
📌戻る際は、股関節から膝までを長くするイメージを持つ事で、中臀筋のストレッチを促します
↩︎
↩︎
お試しあれ♫

E M O T I O N

Is energy in motion, meaning this current emotion you're feeling is not meant to stay with you forever. 

You may have heard the saying, "This too shall pass." 

As a human being you have the wonderful experiences of being content, happiness, and the down right painful experience of emotions. It can make or break us depending on how you have learned to cope with them.

Emotions..
Trigger us
Motivate us
Mold us
And shape us into who we are.

Finding healthy ways to deal with them are one of the biggest gifts you could ever give yourself.

Taking time to acknowledge how you feel in the present moment and being grateful for each and every feeling that passes through you.

I used to be the great represser of emotion because I thought I had to be a certain way. I allowed what I thought other people would think of me to effect the way I reacted to situations. Instead of honoring myself and following through with what I really wanted I lowered my frequency to match someone else's. I avoided confrontation and in return was sabatoging myself and the relationships around me.

I was the person who made sure everyone else was happy except one big issue, I was going against everything my soul really aligned with.

In doing this I lost my grip on life. I would drown out how I felt and numb the built up pain I had been hoarding, all so I seemed a certain way.

It exhausting but you can learn another way.

So I began my healing journey ✨

Tips for a wider & thicker back 👇

💥 focus on #mindmuscleconnection 💥

One of the key things to focus on when training any muscle is to focus on the feel. Your muscles don't care how heavy you are lifting or how many reps you are doing.

Growth is stimulated by pain. Lighten the load, pause at the end of the movement and focus on the squeeze. Control the negative as to stretch the lat and increase #timeundertension 

Lifting heavy is a reward you get when and when you have the mastered perfect form, until then drop the ego and focus on accuracy 👌

How to get stuck back into/start your fitness journey!

4. Remain consistent, don’t throw the towel in at the first hurdle!
5. Ensure the process is enjoyable and your goals are realistic

I hope this helps ladies!

Lower back issues affect many adults over the course of a lifetime so they should be addressed as early as possible.⁠
This weakness can lead to injuries in other parts of the body, most notably the hamstring or quad. ⁠
The sad part is that the causes of back injury can be reduced or even prevented. ⁠
Tips to prevent back pain:⁠
1. Stretch and mobilise the hip flexors daily.⁠
2. Regularly train hip external rotation, glutei medius along with regular glutei Maximus exercises such as RDL and single leg RDL. ⁠
3. Do planks and side planks, working on moving the extremities while preventing any movement of the spine. ⁠
4. Ab crunches can actually increase stress through the lower back depending on the person, so be careful which abdominal exercise you use. ⁠
5. Perform superman isometric holds and progress to horizontal back extension isometric holds with weight. ⁠

「HERE TO MAKE A BETTER YOU」 
Sorry dames en heren, maar er zijn geen oefeningen dat direct buikvet wegwerkt. 

Als je vet wilt verliezen moet je meer kcal verbranden dan je eet en dit doortrekken over een langere periode. 

Als je mij al een tijdje volgt, dan weet je dit vast wel al. Wellicht heb je het ook al geprobeerd. 

Je hebt een kcal onderschot nodig om vet te verliezen, dit is de waarheid en een feit, we noemen dit thermodynamica, dit is een natuurwet en kan je niet omheen, net zoals dat zwaartekracht een feit is. 

Dat wilt nog niet zeggen dat het allemaal zo makkelijk is. Met alle luxe en overvolle supermarkten die we tegenwoordig hebben en alle lekkere dingen en wie vind een macdonalds, kfc of een dikke pizza nou niet soms lekker. 

Ik begrijp het, toch wil het niet zeggen dat je al die dingen moet weglaten om je doelen te behalen. 

Ik focus met mijn klanten op al die factoren zodat je nog altijd kan genieten van je leven zonder dat je alles hoeft op te geven. 

Herken je jezelf hierin? ben je benieuwd wat ik voor je kan betekenen? Stuur gerust een DM en dan kijken we eens naar je doelen!

caption:
✨FIND YOUR WHY✨ 

Here’s your Friday reminder to find your why... it’s easy to feel unmotivated especially when life gets busy!!💗

So I thought I’d share with you guys some of the reasons why I maintain an active, healthy lifestyle even though sometimes the struggle is real...🙌🏻

✨MOOD BOOSTER✨ 
I work from home so my mood lately has become much lower as I don’t get outside or interact with people as often so going to the gym and going on my daily walk on my lunch break allows me to get out the house and I feel so much better afterwards!💪🏼 

✨MORE ENERGY✨ 
Fuelling my body with good nutrients and achieving balance in my diet has always been something I’ve struggled with but lately I’m getting really on top of it and I find myself with more energy to be productive throughout the day, especially helps me wake up earlier in the morning☀️

✨SELF GRATITUDE✨
For me, there’s no better feeling than being proud of something you’ve achieved. Especially if I’ve hit a new PB at the gym or eating more veggies throughout the day! It’s all about the self-love💁🏼‍♀️

Despite the obvious health benefits of being active, these are some of my main ‘whys’💗

Feel free to share yours too because I love to know what other people use as their motivation!🙌🏻

Have a great Friday and weekend💗💗

TRAINING UPPER BODY💪🏼🏋🏻‍♀️

I would avoid training this for the first part of my fitness journey because I thought it would make me look ‘manly’ and ‘bulky’ but I was sooooo wrong!

I’ve been training upper body twice a week for 7 months now and I’m starting to see progress slowly, it is now my favourite body part to train 🤩

I have always had and I don’t use this word often but ‘skinny’ arms, I’ve struggled to gain weight on my arms and it’s taken a lot of hard work but I’m getting stronger!

Never ever neglect your upper bod ladies, get those gains 💪🏼💕

Sorry for the lack of workout vids but I’ve been too busy pushing myself and hitting PBs 😎 for real this week has felt realllly good I think every session I’ve had I’ve hit a fair amount of PBs and I feel so much stronger than before the gyms last closed! 

Since I’ve found @georgiegyms account she has really motivated me to push myself in all my sessions and to remember that you don’t grow in your comfort zone! 

Managed 4 reps on my own on the 14s for shoulder press, progressed to 50kg for Sumos which I’ve been loving and 12s on both hammer & bicep curls oh yeahhh 🤟🏼

Wednesday Nights Legs - Quad Focus
-
Belt squat c/stance top set 185kgX7(5kg up)
C/stance leg press top set 240kgX9(10kg up)
@kayleighadairx belt squat top set 90kgX10(5 reps up☺️😏)
-
Belt squats moved really well on Wednesday, with set increases on all sets whether that be weight or reps. Top set filmed which was an increase of 5kg. Hit for a mid range 7 on top set reps which I will take. Starting to get used to the close stance on the belt squat now to engage more quad activation while allowing the bar at the back to hit the ground. Hopefully keep adding to this, while keeping good form no elbow bends and slow eccentric.
-
Probably one of the best sets I’ve ever done on any form of leg pressing. Slowest tempo on the eccentric phase to date and near enough perfect depth. Anyone can just push a weight back and forth but for the muscle to grow need that time under tension to be lasting longer and controlled. 10kg up on this set as well and capped of straight away with a 9. Will jump up slightly as of next week hoping to maintain this standard of form and tempo.
-
Kayleigh’s top set, definitely surprised herself here, a big 5 rep jump tonight, literally double what she did last week and with much more control and arms staying straight. Keeps improving week in week out just now on everyday and every exercise. Moment I do well she then beats me. Only downside for Kayleigh is new top set weight next week and also back off set as she capped that off for 15 after this🌚🌚🤗🥰.

Once you believe in yourself, you become unstoppable 🙌💪

🖤 Unilateral exercises 🖤

Unilateral exercises are single side, such as lunges or split squats. You have only one side (or limb) working at a time. And they are super good to have in your program!

They’re a great way at identifying and fixing imbalances, and also use a lot more stabilising muscles than a bilateral movement such as a normal squat does. These tend to be muscles we don’t train in isolation so unilateral is a great way to hit them 🔥🔥

They’re also very useful for muscle isolation such as a single arm bicep curl, all your attention is focused on that muscle and movement. This can increase the mind muscle connection which is needed for muscle growth. 

In addition to only moving one side you can unilaterally load your exercises (only hold weight on one side, either the working side or the opposite) which also focuses on your stability and core. 

The downside is they take longer as each set is double the time ⏱

JUST A LITTLE—-
Bit every day! Small habits have big impacts ~ don’t change your whole life over night, remember your health is more important than your size. When you focus on health though, you will prob see your body change too OR at least the way you treat your body.
Right now when I look at the girl on the left I think wow, I’ve changed so much. But guess what! That is exactly what I was thinking when I took the pic on the left initially. I was feeling good about my progress so far and that is really what this about; finding ways to love yourself at every part of your journey, not just the end!

Full back workout... 🏋🏼‍♀️ 

Training back is one of my favourite days in the gym! Here is a full back workout for you to try. This workout can also be done at home with the use of resistance bands/dumbbells.

Seated row - 10-12 reps, 3-4 sets
Lat pull down - 10-12 reps, 3-4 sets
Single arm row - 8-10 reps per arm, 3-4 sets
Superman - 12-15 reps, 3-4 sets 

As usual, reps and sets are just a rough guide. These will always depend on your individual goals and current capabilities, in addition to the weight being used!

✅ I can bench press 15kg for 2 sets of 10 reps, 17.5kg for 2 sets of 8 clean reps, so am going to attempt 20kg in my next session (as long as form is 👌🏼) 

💚 I’ve realised that I get way too in my head with upper body. When training lower I’m always curious and willing to see if I can go a little heavier while maintaining form, whereas with upper body, I don’t even try as I tell myself I’m “way too weak.” 
💚 They may not be big achievements, but the fact I reached for those 7.5s and got them up means a lot to me as it shows I’ve held myself back somewhat! 
💚 Aaaand I’ve also learned that bench press is actually so fun and feels so good so I REALLY want to keep working on it. Any tips, especially form oriented are always appreciated 🤩

Hey waddup hello🤍✨

Hope everyone has a lovely Friday & a lovely weekend! 
I’m spending mine working, I recently got a second job as a children’s rugby coach and i start my training Tommorow! 🤪

What are you up to this weekend ?!💓

1 week difference😅

Even when you think you’re not making progress.. you are.

I mean, yeah we have a SLIGHT change in lighting here. It must’ve been the fact I got up at 7am one week, and then 7:10am the following week🤣 it’s natty lighting for gods sake, with no editing- you ain’t getting much more ‘natty’ than that 🤣🤥

But yeah, just saying- the body is a weird and wonderful thing. Especially when you’re dieting. Being on a deficit for so an extensive period of time now and making consistent progress towards my goal, throwing in an ‘off week’ on the diet side of things hasn’t hindered me in any way I don’t think really.

If anything.. it looks like it’s benefitted me🤷🏼‍♂️ don’t get me wrong though, this ain’t a ‘ahh off week every week and you’ll get shredded’- nah bro, not how it works unfortunately.

It’s either the ‘off week’, or it’s the grey boxers🤷🏼‍♂️ I’ll let you decide 🤣

But yeah, that’s it from me. Back to the game plan in full force and feeling great, going to spend some time today prepping food for the week so there is no excuse 😅

Have a great week!

Inner strength is your ability to look inside yourself and see your potential, using all you have to reach your goals and to overcome obstacles. It is your resilience, your ability to bounce back after setbacks. Inner strength requires a growth mindset, a willingness to get outside your comfort zone in order to change and improve.

Goals should never be easy to reach – whether big or small. They take courage, determination, and perseverance. Most of us have had goals that have gone unreached; not because we were not capable, but because we didn’t dig deep enough to realise our potential. We quit because we think we are unworthy or unable. Motivation comes and goes but discipline will allow us to push forwards and use failures as lessons to succeed. 

Remember, it doesn’t matter how many times you get knocked down. All that matters is you get up one more time and increase your own odds – this is YOUR fight, make it count.

💛1.5 YEAR PROGRESS...💛.
•
⚠️TW: talk of weight, fat, calories, food & body shape! Please do not read this if it’ll do you more harm than good! I’ll be posting again tomorrow!⚠️.
•
Gooooood morning everyone! Happy Friday!
•
Today I wanted to talk about my “transformation” & the progress I have made in the gym! This is actually quite difficult for me to talk about as it requires me to be fully open about things I’m not so comfortable with! However, I know it’s important!

In the right photo, I didn’t realise how unhealthy & cruel I was to my body. Believe it or not, I used to think I was “overweight” in this photo! Now, I look back & see that I was unhealthy. I was basically starving my body. I worked out that I was eating around 1500 calories a day, then burning about 500 in the gym 4 times a week... I was basically in taking around 1000 calories a day... WHAT THE HELL!? No wonder I couldn’t get my hipthrusts heavier than 60kg! I WAS LITERALLY STARVING MYSELF!

In the left photo, which was taken about 4 days ago now, I am healthy. I’m not starving myself. I’m fuelling my body to be able to get stronger & actually function properly! Yes, I’ve gained some fat, but I’ve been growing my muscles, getting stronger & learning to care for my body, like it deserves to be! I can even see that I am healthier now!

I found this picture because I have been bullying myself recently about how much fat I’ve gained over the last few months. YES, I always talk about how it’s not good to have an aesthetic goal, but my brain has been conditioned to be this way by society, LIKE MOST PEOPLE! I’m starting to actually listen to my own words! I know I am healthier now & so do my loved ones around me! I just needed to see that for myself, hence why I’ve put these photos side by side!

ALSO, just wanna hype myself about those booty gains thoooo 🤪! It’s okay to praise yourself! Apologies that it’s not the same outfit, but like hell would I be able to fit into those leggings now 😂!

Any comments like “I preferred you before” or anything like that will be deleted so feel free to waste your time🙃!

Wanneer je voor je gevoel wilt stoppen, herinner jezelf eraan waarom je bent begonnen. 

Iets waar ik vaak aan denk. Omdat het voor mijn gevoel niet snel genoeg gaat heb ik vaak punt bereikt wanneer ik denk dat stoppen toch niet uit zou maken. Gelukkig ben ik niet gestopt, en dat ben ik ook nog even niet van plan! Ik ga door tot het bittere eind, tot het punt dat ik “de nieuwe Viv” heb bereikt. Dat is mijn doel.

Nog even wat anders zo tussendoor. Ik wil iedere volger van mij zo erg bedanken voor de steun en support! Ik vind het echt zo gaaf om te zien dat ik andere kan helpen en dat ik ook geholpen wordt door degene die ik volg. Dat dit allemaal mogelijk is en gebeurd is ook wel echt iets wat mij op de been houdt om mijn doelen te behalen! Puur omdat ik mijn reis dan weer met jullie kan delen. Iedereen.. bedankt voor jullie support! I’m speechless!

Thought I’d post a progress pic since I’m just over halfway through my training plan! But also, when I look at these 2 pics I actually don’t see much difference between them, apart from that I’ve gained a bit of weight which was my goal. 

HOWEVER, I know that I’ve been getting stronger each week and lifting heavier over time, so I’m not going to let the lack of difference in the pictures mess with my head, because I HAVE made progress, it’s just not really that visible from these pics 😤

𝘉𝘭𝘶𝘦𝘣𝘦𝘳𝘳𝘺 𝘉𝘪𝘴𝘤𝘰𝘧𝘧 𝘣𝘢𝘬𝘦𝘥 𝘰𝘢𝘵𝘴:
Blend together
• 30 grams of oats
• 1 small banana 🍌 
• 1/2 teaspoon baking powder
• Nutmeg, cinnamon, biscoff spice
• Pinch of salt
• 1/3 cup almond milk
• white chocolate sweetener drops (or a tablespoon of maple syrup)

Filling:
• blueberries
• Biscoff spread

Pour 1/2 of the mixture into a ramekin.
Put a dollop of Biscoff spread in the middle and throw some blueberries in there as well. Sprinkle with some cinnamon before adding the remaining batter and put in the oven for 20 mins on 180 Celsius/ 356 Fahrenheit.
Now pour some extra almond milk milk on top , add some extra blueberries and finish it all off with puffed rice. Yum!
